definitions.definition: To produce offspring sexually ; to bear young .
To give birth to; to be the native place of.
examples: A northern country breeds stout men.

definitions.definition: To keep ( animals ) and have (them) reproduce in a way that improves the next generation 's qualities .
To arrange the mating of (specific animals).
examples: She wanted to breed her cow to the neighbor's registered bull.
definitions.label_groups: transitive , often with to or with

definitions.definition: To propagate or grow ( plants ) in an effort to give (them) certain qualities .
examples: He tries to breed blue roses.

definitions.definition: To take care of in infancy and through childhood ; to bring up .
To be formed in the parent or dam ; to be generated or to grow , like young before birth .
To educate ; to instruct ; to bring up .
To produce or obtain by any natural process .
To have birth ; to be produced , developed , or multiplied .
To ejaculate inside (a person or a bodily orifice of same); to creampie .
